                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d754">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">862.857/85: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Panama</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-03-06T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 6, 1940—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>26. Your 29, March 6, 10 a.m. In view of the fact that the Declaration of Panama
                    and the statement of December 23 were transmitted by the President of Panama to
                    the King of England, the Department perceives no objection to a modification of
                    the text of the protest proposed by the Brazilian Government so as to provide
                    for its transmission in the same manner.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
